Chilopselaphus numidellus was described from an unspecified number of specimens (probably more than one as the wingspan is stated to be "15- 16 mm") collected at Gafsa in Tunisia in May. It was compared with C. fallax Mann (
Chretien 1915
). We have been able to examine photographs of a syntype from MNHN. This specimen is here designated as the lectotype in order to fix the identity of the species and conserve stability of nomenclature. Megacraspedus mareotidellus was described from eleven specimens collected at El Berca, Benghazi, Libya ( Turati 1924 : 169). It was compared with "oranellus B.H.", but we have been unable to trace this name in the literature. A male labelled as a paralectotype by K Sattler and considered to be a syntype fully corresponds with figures of a syntype of M. numidellus and we thus consider M. mareotidellus to be a junior synonym of the former (syn. n.).
